{"_id":"eLj0eMJgZkFGp9JQ","name":"Conceal Self","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"1d10","rollType":"above","rollTarget":2,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>Snipers are masters of camouflage and concealment. Any time a Sniper is by himself (or with another Sniper) and has time to conceal himself, he may <strong>only be detected on a 1 in 10 chance </strong>if someone is actively searching for him (if the searcher is another Sniper, use the Spot Ambush rules instead).</p>\n<p>This chance increases by a cumulative <strong>+1 for every round </strong>the Sniper attacks from that position.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"3wiJ967CCavATyv3","name":"Contacts","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"1d20","rollType":"above","rollTarget":4,"blindroll":true,"description":"<p>Maquis characters naturally develop a number of political, military, and civilian contacts over the course of their lives. Once per day, whenever the character is in France, he may receive information or assistance from one of these contacts. The Referee is free to determine the nature of these contacts and the assistance they can provide.</p>\n<p>The Referee should secretly roll 1d20 any time a contact is approached. On a roll of 2-3, the information or assistance is faulty. On a roll of \"1\", it is outright wrong.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"u24T801d6mvQRVG0","name":"Demolitions","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>All special forces operatives are trained in the use of plastic explosives and other ordnance.</p>\n<p>The Combat Engineer is additionally skilled in the use of advanced techniques such as blowing safes, doors, and even buildings with little to no damage to the contents or surroundings.</p>\n<p>When Static Explosives are used to cause damage to persons or vehicles, the Combat Engineer <strong>doubles</strong> the amount of damage delivered.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"kvlMJaNYEXZPAzcw","name":"Detect Deception","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>Once a Charmer reaches 3rd level, he has become so good at reading people that he becomes a master at detecting deception (body language, nervous tics, outright lies, etc.).</p>\n<p>After speaking with a person for three (3) rounds, the Charmer may make a <strong>Saving Throw</strong> in order to detect any lie or deception. This roll is influenced by the difference between the Charmer's <strong>Experience Level</strong> and the target's Experience Level.</p>","save":"true"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Zr4aOIDobM9kuSGR","name":"Fast and Furious","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>At the beginning of each Vehicle Combat round, a Wheelman operating a vehicle may temporarily add<strong> +1 </strong>to any one of the <strong>vehicle's Armor Class, Movement, To-Hit, or Weapon Damage</strong>. He may choose which statistic to modify each round, selecting a different one each time. At 3rd level a Wheelman may add a total of +2 to any combination of the vehicle's statistics each round. At 5th level a Wheelman may add a total of +3 to any combination of the vehicle&rsquo;s statistics each round.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"6pqUCUtDRZaVLdnr","name":"Friendly Demeanour","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>The Charmer is so gracious and disarming that he receives a +1 bonus to any Reaction Roll made by him or his companions. This bonus increases to +2 when dealing with members of the opposite sex.</p>\n<p>At 3rd level, this bonus increases to +2 (+3 with opposite sex).</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"wZFIEAIc489nBbu4","name":"Gearhead","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>Once a Wheelman reaches 3rd level he may modify his vehicle beyond its stock Statistics. This includes adding weapons, armor, speed, modifications, etc. How long this takes and what it involves are determined by the Referee.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"QgnCbTiBBCdr64g0","name":"Hero's Welcome","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"2d6","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>Once an &Uuml;berl&auml;ufer reaches 3rd level, the people of his homeland consider him a hero.<strong> 2d6</strong> young men from his hometown (or village, city, etc.) join the Allied forces and are assigned to assist the &Uuml;berl&auml;ufer. If the character manages to survive the war, he is sure to return home with honor.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"LgzoE2ubdQ2QWyBI","name":"Jury-rig","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>Three times per day, a Combat Engineer may attempt a quick fix on a piece of machinery (such as a radio, weapon, or vehicle).</p>\n<p>These temporary repairs tend to break down quickly and in some cases can lead to the item's destruction.</p>\n<p>Jury-Rig takes one (1) round and restores a number of Hit Points to the item equal to 1d6 per Experience Level of the Combat Engineer.</p>\n<p>After 2d6 turns, the item suffers damage equal to the same amount restored by Jury-Rig.</p>\n<p>If the item does not have Hit Points, it functions normally for 2d6 rounds before overheating, warping, short-circuiting, or otherwise becoming useless.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"gajBcBlFf7C5kXCb","name":"Legendary Sniper","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"1d3","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>The Sniper is a decorated hero whose reputation precedes him wherever he goes.</p>\n<p>He becomes responsible for training<strong> 1d3</strong> 1st-level Snipers who can accompany him on missions.</p>\n<p>If enemy troops learn that the Sniper character is operating in the area, it has a detrimental effect on their morale. All enemy combatants that are not behind full cover suffer a <strong>-1 To-Hit </strong>during any combat because they are so fearful of being picked off while out in the open.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"IjNdFPwfb5a4HIHt","name":"Loyal Allies","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"1d6","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>The Charmer's friendly demeanor draws the service of <strong>1d6</strong> loyal NPCs. These allies are fiercely loyal to the Charmer and assist him in any way possible, even fighting and dying for him, if necessary. The player and the Referee should work together to determine the nature of these NPCs and how they came to idolize the Charmer.</p>\n<p>They may be civilians, fellow soldiers, resistance fighters, or even disillusioned German fighters that the Charmer has aided, armed, or rescued.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"QM4Nf3x96KFI0n08","name":"Mechanical Understanding","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>Combat Engineers have a natural understanding of all things technical and mechanical. At the Referee&rsquo;s discretion, they may receive bonuses or increased chances of success when dealing with machinery and technology such as vehicles, weapons, and radios.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"gQqKpUv2gEACPVa3","name":"Nazi Hate","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>The &Uuml;berl&auml;ufer was conscripted by the Nazis and forced to fight, often after threats to his home and family. Because of this, &Uuml;berl&auml;ufer characters harbor a deep resentment for the German Army, and a particular hatred for the Nazi Party.</p>\n<p>&Uuml;berl&auml;ufer's receive<strong> +1 To-Hit when fighting Germans</strong>, and <strong>+2 To-Hit when fighting Nazis</strong>. This bonus increases to +2/+3 when the &Uuml;berl&auml;ufer reaches 5th level.</p>\n<p>When forced to interact closely with a Nazi such as a Gestapo agent or Waffen-SS officer, the &Uuml;berl&auml;ufer <strong>must make a Saving Throw to avoid attacking them outright.</strong></p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"wCeRPjbq20ROrnam","name":"Preferred Weapon","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>The Sniper chooses a preferred missile weapon to specialize in (typically a Large Rifle).</p>\n<p>Using this weapon grants the Sniper a +1 <strong>bonus To-Hit and damage</strong> at 1st level, a +2 bonus To-Hit and damage at 3rd level, and a +3 bonus To-Hit and damage at 5th level when firing single shots.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"O4gYEpTcK2CkZTHy","name":"Rally","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>The Tactician is able to rally his men through words and deeds. Often this is done by a rousing speech before a battle commences or by barking out orders and showing disdain for the enemy in the midst of the fighting.</p>\n<p>Rally takes one (1) round to initiate. It grants the Tactician's allies a -1 [+1] bonus to their Armor Class and +1 To-Hit. At 3rd level, this bonus increases to -2 [+2] Armor Class and +2 To-Hit.</p>\n<p>This ability may be used a number of times per day equal to the Tactician's Experience Level and the effects last for six (6) turns.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"XsUK2vEmSOQVLSNM","name":"Resistance Leader","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>The Maquis character is recognized as a leader of the French resistance. <strong>Once per mission</strong>, the character can call up the assistance of <strong>1d6 </strong>partisans willing to fight, as well as another <strong>3d6 </strong>sympathizers who are willing to provide aid, lodging, and assistance to the Maquis character on a moment's notice.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"yF7VKuuNpp7EMQpL","name":"Smooth Operator","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>The Charmer is a smooth talker who can influence others just by speaking to them. The Charmer must speak the language of the person he is trying to influence and can only influence one person at a time.</p>\n<p>If the Charmer talks to the person for one (1) round, the target must make a Saving Throw. If the roll fails, the target believes the Charmer to be an honest friend and ally.</p>\n<p>The target believes any plausible lie and may even risk his life to protect the Charmer. This effect lasts until the Charmer betrays the NPC or there is overwhelming evidence that the Charmer is an enemy.</p>","save":"true"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ezeHEFQbRArWA6k6","name":"Spot Ambush","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>Snipers are so skilled at setting ambushes that they have an uncanny ability to detect them as well.</p>\n<p>A Sniper character that is actively searching for possible ambushes has a 1 in 3 chance of detecting them (1 in 6 chance if looking for another Sniper). At 3rd level, this chance increases to 2 in 3 (3 in 6 if looking for another Sniper). Other factors may modify this chance&nbsp;to spot an ambush, at the Referee&rsquo;s discretion.</p>\n<p>The Sniper cannot move faster than 1/2 his normal Movement rate while searching for ambushes.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"JQuLIB19HAv0hTmf","name":"Superior Planner","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>The Tactician is a master planner who can point out the strengths and weaknesses in any plan. When the Tactician has time to analyze the plan for an upcoming mission, the Referee should make suggestions and point out any obvious flaws in the plan or possible complications that might arise, based on the current intel.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"0LbzeSUDRvuUr54k","name":"Tech-master","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>Once a Combat Engineer reaches 3rd level, he becomes an expert on the latest technology and inventions (including Covert Special Forces Equipment, pg. 92). In addition, the Combat Engineer may modify equipment and weapons beyond their stock Statistics. This includes increasing damage, range, functionality, Armor Class, etc. How long this takes and what it involves are determined by the Referee.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"BZzhRUlhLnLhAdsV","name":"Uncanny Toughness","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>A Grunt is capable of avoiding attacks and shrugging off injuries that would incapacitate or kill a lesser man. A Grunt receives a -1 [+1] <strong>bonus to his Armor Class</strong> at 1st level, a -2 [+2] bonus to his Armor Class at 3rd level, and a -3 [+3] bonus to his Armor Class at 5th level.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"AyYppTzDMG9aWnQG","name":"Vehicle Understanding","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>Wheelmen have a natural understanding of ground vehicles (cars, trucks, tanks, etc.). At the Referee&rsquo;s discretion, they may receive bonuses or increased chances of success when dealing with service and repair of vehicles.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Au6BGXk9aQuFxlOF","name":"Wehrmacht Understanding","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>&Uuml;berl&auml;ufers were conscripted by the Germans and are familiar with the inner workings of the German military. At the Referee&rsquo;s discretion, they may receive bonuses or increased chances of success when attempting to locate or deal with anything related to the German military, including its ranks, tactics, and customs. This information can prove extremely beneficial when drafting mission plans.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"GNoMuRWS7MvOIVb2","name":"Wilderness Survival","permission":{"default":0,"2ins83sY7CMjwWHS":3},"type":"ability","data":{"pattern":"white","requirements":"","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p>The &Uuml;berl&auml;ufer spent weeks living off the land as he traversed occupied territory. He has a keen sense of direction and is particularly adept at surviving in the wild, hunting game, and finding isolated places to camp and hide from German patrols.</p>","save":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/owb/assets/default/abilities.png","effects":[]}
